                type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 11, 1951, the Board of Directors of the Export–Import Bank had
                    authorized a credit of $1,503,000 to the National Railways of Colombia to
                    finance the purchase of five Diesel electric locomotives and spare parts in the
                    United States (821.10/1–1851). For further information, see Export–Import Bank
                    of Washington. <hi rend="italic">Twelfth Semiannual Report to Congress for the
                        Period January–June 1951</hi> (Washington, 1951), pages 11–12, 36.</p>
                <p>On November 1, 1951, the Board of Directors of the Export-Import Bank established
                    a line of credit up to $20,000,000 in favor of the Colombian Bank of the
                    Republic or such commercial banks as it might designate to finance the purchase
                    and shipment of raw cotton from the United States to Colombia (821.10/11–151).
                    For further information of this loan, see Export–Import Bank of Washington, <hi
                        rend="italic">Thirteenth Semiannual Report to Congress for the Period
                        July–December 1951</hi> (Washington, 1952), pages 14, 36. For a Department
                    of State notice concerning the loan, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, November 19, 1951, page 828.</p>
            </div>
